{{Infobox event | title = Vandellòs I Nuclear Incident | image = Instal·lacions nuclears de Vandellòs I.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = Remaining facilities of the [[Vandellòs Nuclear Power Plant|Vandellòs I Nuclear Power Plant]] in 2013. The blue structure, designed to blend into the background, contains the decaying [[nuclear reactor]]. | date = {{start date|1989|10|19}} | location = | coordinates = {{Coord |40|57|18|N|0|52|34|E| display=inline}} | type = [[International Nuclear Event Scale|INES]] Level 3: Serious incident. Collapse of the refrigeration system | cause = Fire in the [[electric generator]] | participants = | outcome = [[Nuclear decommissioning]] of Vandellòs I Power Plant and new safety protocols introduced (plans for the evacuation of civilians, emergency drills...) | charges = 5 high ranks of Hispano Francesa de Energía Nuclear SA (Hifrensa) accused of risk of omission | trial = 1999 | verdict = All charges absolved alleging it was a design error<ref name="Girona">{{cite news |editor= ACN/DDG |date= 2009 |title= Vandellòs I, vint anys de records latents |trans-title= Vandellòs I, twenty years of latent memories |url= http://www.diaridegirona.cat/catalunya/2009/10/18/vandellos-vint-anys-records-latents/364247.html |language= Catalan |work= [[Diari de Girona]] |access-date= 20 October 2017}}</ref> }}
'''Vandellòs I Nuclear Accident''' was a fire that caused an interruption of the refrigeration system in the nuclear reactor of [[Vandellòs Nuclear Power Plant|Vandellòs]], [[Catalonia]] (Spain) on 19 October 1989.<ref name="CCMA">{{cite news |editor= Redacció |date= 19 October 2014|title= Fa 25 anys del greu accident a la central nuclear Vandellòs 1 |trans-title= 25 years since the serious accident at Vandellòs I Nuclear Power Plant |url= http://www.ccma.cat/324/Fa-25-anys-del-greu-accident-a-la-central-nuclear-Vandellos-1/noticia/2506894/ |language= Catalan |work= [[Corporació Catalana de Mitjans Audiovisuals]] |location= Vandellòs |access-date= 20 October 2017}}</ref>
At the end of the [[Franco regime]], France sold Spain a [[UNGG reactor]]. This already obsolete energy technology was installed because as a [[by-product]] it provided [[plutonium]] that could be used to manufacture [[atomic bombs]].<ref name="Ara">{{cite news |last= Solé |first= Albert |date= 18 October 2014 |title= «25 anys de l'incendi de Vandellòs I: la central construïda per fer bombes nuclears franceses |trans-title= 25 years since Vandellòs I fire: the power plant built to make French nuclear bombs |url= http://www.ara.cat/societat/vandellos_I-central_nuclear-accident-incendi-25_anys_0_1231676995.html |language= Catalan |work= [[Ara (newspaper)|Diari Ara]] |location= |access-date= 20 October 2017}}</ref> Vandellòs I Nuclear Power Plant was inaugurated in 1972 when there were only two operational nuclear power plants in Spain: [[Santa María de Garoña Nuclear Power Plant|Garoña]] and [[José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station|Zorita]]. Seventeen years after opening, the rudimentary technology produced a mechanical failure in the [[gas turbine]] which caused a fire. The cabling of the plant was not [[fireproof]] and the control computer and the refrigeration system would also receive damage.<ref>{{cite news |last= Sans |first= Sara |date= 20 October 2009 |title= Los residuos de la central nuclear Vandellòs I aún no tienen destino |trans-title= The waste of Vandellòs I nuclear power plant has not yet reached its destination |url= http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/motociclismo/20091019/53806113299/los-residuos-de-la-central-nuclear-vandellos-i-aun-no-tienen-destino.html |language= Spanish |work= [[La Vanguardia]] |access-date= 20 October 2017}}</ref>
The [[Nuclear meltdown|core meltdown]] was avoided due to the intervention of the [[Corps of Firefighters of Catalonia]] and the plant technicians, which were able to extinguish the fire and turn off the nuclear reactor manually. It continues to be one of the biggest nuclear accidents in [[Western Europe]], classified as a serious incident according to the [[International Nuclear Event Scale]]. As a consequence, the plant would be [[Nuclear decommissioning|decommissioned]], due to the damage in the systems, and new safety protocols were introduced, because the old ones proved to be inefficient.<ref>{{cite news |last= Pérez Pons |first= Mercè |date= 18 October 2010 |title= La nit més llarga de Vandellòs |trans-title= The longest night in Vandellòs |url= https://cat.elpais.com/cat/2014/10/18/catalunya/1413655337_690826.html |language= Catalan |work= [[El País]] |access-date= 20 October 2017}}</ref>
